    "content_hash": "5c19acee45b7fd29",
    "department": "Alliances and Channels",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\nWe're looking for a Partner Development Manager to join our EMEA team and lead our new, strategic partnership with SAP. This is a unique opportunity for a motivated and experienced professional with a builder's mentality to shape and grow a critical alliance from the ground up. You will be instrumental in defining our joint go-to-market strategy, driving co-sell opportunities, and enabling our field teams to succeed. This role requires a blend of business acumen, experience, technical understanding, and exceptional relationship-building skills.\n\nWhat you will do:\n\n - Strategy \u0026 GTM: Develop and execute a comprehensive go-to-market plan for the SAP partnership across EMEA. Identify key target industries, use cases, and joint solutions.\n\n - Relationship Management: Build and maintain strong, executive-level relationships with key stakeholders at SAP, including sales leadership, product teams, and alliance counterparts. Proactively build trust-based relationships across both internal, SAP stakeholders and mutualSI \u0026 ISV Partners.\n\n - Pipeline Generation: Drive joint pipeline and revenue growth through co-selling, co-marketing initiatives, and strategic account mapping. Track and report on key performance indicators (KPIs) related to the partnership.\n\n - Field Enablement: Act as the primary liaison between our sales teams and SAP's field organisation. Equip our sales reps with the knowledge, tools, and resources needed to effectively sell with SAP.\n\n - Work with regional Snowflake and SAP marketing teams to execute compelling marketing programs that highlight the value of Snowflake and Snowflake + SAP joint solutions\n\n - Program Management: Lead the day-to-day operational cadence of the partnership, including regular business reviews, QBRs, and internal reporting.\n\n - Thought Leadership: Represent the partnership at industry events, conferences, and internal meetings.\n\n - Work closely with Global Snowflake colleagues along with teams from the Americas and APJ who are aligned with the SAP partnership to achieve annual sales targets\n   \n   Who you are:\n\n - A seasoned professional with 10+ years of experience in alliance management, partner development, or business development, with a strong focus on enterprise software. Prior background in software and SaaS\n\n - Ideally based out of Walldorf, Baden-Württemberg, Germany.\n\n - You have proven, recent experience working directly with SAP in an alliance or partnership capacity. You understand SAP’s ecosystem, organisational structure, and go-to-market motions. 3+ years of experience working SAP as a partner\n\n - You possess a builder's mentality, comfortable with ambiguity and eager to create something new. You are a self-starter who can operate independently and drive results.\n\n - You have a deep understanding of data platforms, cloud technology, and the analytics landscape. and data driven strategic thinker, capable of creative problem solving and pragmatic execution\n\n - You are an exceptional communicator and presenter, able to articulate complex value propositions to diverse audiences.\n\n - You are a highly collaborative team player who can influence without authority and work effectively across internal and external teams.\n\n - Travel will be required for this role as we build and grow the partnership.\n\n - History of success in working with cross-functional team members, including Sales, Sales Engineering, Finance, Marketing and Programs\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
